{
  "text": "More specifically, as shown in Fig. 1(c) , a narrow TOBPF is included before the EDF for each channel. The transmission peak of the TOBFP is much narrower than the reflection bandwidth of the corresponding FBG so that the fiber laser wavelength is determined by the TOBFP. To perform ultrasonic detection, the center wavelength of the TOBFP is tuned on a spectral slope of the FBG. The ultrasonic signal that impinges onto the FBG causes the spectral shift of the FBG spectrum, which in turn modulates the cold cavity loss of this particular channel of the FRL. It has been theoretically and experimentally demonstrated that the FRL power fluctuates according to the loss modulation [CITATION_1] . Therefore, the ultrasonic signal that impinges on a particular FBG can be detected from the variations of the laser output power of the corresponding FRL channel, which is monitored by a PD through a fiberoptic coupler.",
  "citation_candidates": [
